ODM leader Raila Odinga on Wednesday condemned the violence witnessed in Migori on Monday.He said the party will not tolerate political hooliganism and/ or thuggery. Raila accused a section of leaders from the area of inciting supporters to cause mayhem."Whoever is responsible for the incident will be severely dealt with by the party," he said in Nairobi.During the scuffle at Posta grounds, Mombasa Governor Hassan Joho's bodyguard wasshot.It is alleged the shot was fired by a member of Migori Governor Okoth Obado's security detail.Obado had reportedly threatened to prevent ODM from holding a rally in the town. The two were reconciled on Tuesday following a meeting at Raila's Capitol Hill office. More on this: Joho bodyguard shot during chaotic ODM rally in Migori Joho accused trained security officials of attempting to assassinate ODM leaders.Mvita MP Abdulswamad Nassir told the Star: "This was an assassination attempt. They were after Joho. Our car was shot at three times."In a statement, Joho said the alleged assassination had been conducted by experts who wanted to harm the leaders.Also read: Migori attack 'an assassination attempt' by trained security officers - JohoDuring the Tuesday talks, the two governors agreed to hold free and fair nominations.Joho, who is ODM deputy leader, further assured members that the party has no preferred candidates.